      • setAckExpirationPadding

        public Subscriber.Builder setAckExpirationPadding(org.joda.time.Duration ackExpirationPadding)
        Set acknowledgement expiration padding.

        This is the time accounted before a message expiration is to happen, so the Subscriber is able to send an ack extension beforehand.

        This padding duration is configurable so you can account for network latency. A reasonable number must be provided so messages don't expire because of network latency between when the ack extension is required and when it reaches the Pub/Sub service.

        Parameters:
        ackExpirationPadding - must be greater or equal to MIN_ACK_EXPIRATION_PADDING
